Yobe state Governor Mai Mala Buni, has met with the Minister of Transportation Rotimi Ameachi and the Managing Director of the Nigerian Shippers’ Council Hassan Bello to advance effort to commence the construction of the Potiskum Truck Transit Park otherwise known as the Potiskum Trailer Park. The meeting took place in Abuja, the Potiskum Truck Transit Park was conceived by the Buni administration to provide a modern hub for the thriving trailer transportation business in Potiskum and environs and standardise and enhance the trucking value chain in the state. LEADERSHIP recalls that, the governor laid the foundation stone for the construction of the Park on 4th September 2919 in partnership with the Nigerian Shippers’ Council. According to the governor, the Projected will create more than 5000 direct jobs, the Potiskum Trailer Park would have hotels, fuel dispensing stations, shops, a recreational area, and a mechanics’ village, amongst others. Governor Buni, Minister Ameachi and the Shippers’ Council boss Hassan Bello reviewed the progress made in the Park’s construction partnership and discussed timelines for when construction work could begin. The partnership, the Shippers’ Council would spearhead effort to attract and engage investors in establishing the Park with all its attendant services. He added that, ” the Potiskum Truck Transit Park is going to support up to 5000 direct jobs, the jobs and their positive spin-offs will certainly transform wealth creation In Yobe State and improve the economy overall”, said Buni.